pr_review_body:
@ChipKerchner Thank you and all people who were working on this PR so much for all your hard work and patience! We really appreciate this valuable contribution!
I don't have any other comments.

@jameslamb Please update your `requested changes` review status.

@PLLamure thanks a lot for your contribution.
I have submitted a first round of comments with some questions.
Please address also the errors raised by lint.

Thank you!
Plus, how about this idea?
Since all managers have its own id, we can update and fetch each manager's scheduler state. Let's discuss about this.
If we implement this idea, the data under "manager" key in etcd would be like this.
```
{
  "manager": {
    "MANAGER-ID-1": {
      "schedule": {
        "execution-time": "",
        "finish-time": "",
        "scaling-group-name": ""
      },
      "prepare": {
        "execution-time": "",
        "finish-time": "",
        "scaling-group-name": ""
      },
      "scale": {
        "execution-time": "",
        "finish-time": "",
        "scaling-group-name": ""
      },
    }
  }
}
```

This is quite a lot of code and lines changed `+436 −178` to ultimately make it so that we can override a default plugins directory.

It's my preference if there a way to add a default plugins directory env var without making too many changes here.

@Frassle I know you tend to have opinions on things like these. WDYT?

@jameslamb Thanks a lot for cleaning up aliases handling logic!
LGTM except one typo that you've already mentioned earlier
> replaces mistaken parameter name "listen_time_out" with "time_out"

@pb-new-username: Left you some comments/feedback. Specifically, I don't believe we can use DataFrames since there are no headers. perhaps you have a working example. Also have a comment on expected data. 

I like this call though. We should see if there's some way of getting into the details of a specific day as to not have to load the entire year. Look forward to chatting.

Also. Saw you have a PR against my branch (rsforbes) and this branch (swar), is this the same PR? perhaps you can open this against main since Live was merged. Just a thought.
